list.abstract: vehicle，读音为[ˈviːəkl]，英语单词，名词，意思有交通工具、手段、公司等。近义词有“instrument”“tool”。组词有“electric vehicle”“launch vehicle”。例句为“Obviously Don had somehow made the vehicle move”。 vehicle的复数形式为vehicles，motor vehicle意思为汽车、机动车。

yingyinNormal.en: However, our examination of the vehicle did reveal a small amount of blood on the passenger side dashboard.
yingyinNormal.zh: 然而，我们检查了车辆并且在副驾驶仪表盘上发现了少量血液。

yingyinNormal.en: How's your little lorry? Little lorry? My breakdown truck is a proper work vehicle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的这台小卡车怎么样啦？什么？小卡车？我的这辆拖车可是一辆真正的工作车辆。

yingyinNormal.en: A terrifying development today as a vehicle matching that of a missing San Jose teenager was discovered late last night underneath a Santa Cruz lake.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今天事情有了不好的进展，与一名来自圣何塞的青少年匹配的车辆昨夜发现沉于圣克鲁斯湖底。

yingyinNormal.en: This entire facility's a centrifuge. Some kind of vehicle. A space station? Both. Plan A.
yingyinNormal.zh: 整个设施就是个大型离心机，是运输工具，还是空间站？都是，这是A计划。

yingyinNormal.en: The internet is this amazing distribution vehicle to get people's ideas into people's homes and workplace.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而网络则是让人们的灵感在千家万户乃至工作场地得以实现的渠道。

yingyinNormal.en: So unless you want dear Nathaniel to know how you lost your virginity to me in the back of a moving vehicle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 除非你想让亲爱的内特尼尔知道你是怎么在车后座被我夺去处女之身的。

yingyinNormal.en: And you have a vehicle? A car, yeah. And you'll be willing to drive me? Can't you drive? I can. I choose not to.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你有交通工具吗？有辆车。你愿意载我吗？你不会开车吗？我会，我不想开。

yingyinNormal.en: I have NCIC searching for the vehicle in 16 states. Let's both try and catch up on some sleep tonight. Talk in the a.m.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我已让NCIC在十六个州中搜索这辆车。我们今晚都休息一下。明早再联络。

yingyinNormal.en: Did it work? No. We need a vehicle with more power. Can I help in any way? It's nothing that I can't deal with. Thanks anyway.
yingyinNormal.zh: 成功了吗？没有。我们需要一辆马力更大的车子。有什么需要我帮忙的吗？没有什么事是我解决不了的。但还是谢谢你啦。

yingyinNormal.en: Next time, you want to leave town after betraying your country, how about you steal a car, to take you to your get away vehicle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 下次叛国后想逃跑的时候，记得先偷辆车开过来换你平时用的车。

yingyinNormal.en: Actually, we're not. And perhaps you could express a little more concern over the fact that you stole and destroyed a $19 million vehicle. Bill me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 其实，我们不是。而且，你应该稍微关心一下你们偷窃并且毁掉一架价值一千九百万飞机的事实！账单寄给我！

yingyinNormal.en: An operation is currently underway to recover Margot Kim's Toyota Camry. But at this moment, we still don't know whether the Evercreek High sophomore is actually inside the vehicle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 正在进行玛戈·金驾驶的丰田凯美瑞打捞工作。但目前，仍不清楚是否这位埃弗克里克高二学生在车中。

yingyinNormal.en: That is yours to circulate. But focusing on the events of this morning, The Silicon Valley Police Department was able to recover Ms. Kim's vehicle. And to answer the most pressing question, Margot Kim was not inside.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是你们都知道的。重点在今天早上发生的事情，硅谷的警察局打捞上了金女士的车。回答目前最急切的问题玛戈·金不在车里。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: The coming use of autonomous <highlight>vehicles</highlight>, for example, poses thorny ethical questions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，即将使用的自动驾驶汽车带来了棘手的伦理问题。

examination_example.sentence: The advance is driven in part by <highlight>vehicle</highlight> manufacturers, who are placing big bets on battery-powered electric vehicles.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这一进步部分是由汽车制造商推动的，他们在电池驱动的电动汽车上下了很大的赌注。

examination_example.sentence: Legislation is moving through the House, which could help pay for new <highlight>vehicles</highlight>, among other survival measures.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 众议院正在通过一项法案，该法案可能将有助于购买新的交通工具及其他生存设施。

sense_info_list.en: a thing used to express, embody, or fulfill something

examination_example.sentence: The spirit of inquiry has been replaced by the social sciences as <highlight>vehicles</highlight> for publicizing "progressive," or left-liberal propaganda.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 探究精神已经被社会科学取代，成为宣传“进步”或鼓吹左翼自由主义的工具。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Researchers are already asking if motor <highlight>vehicle</highlight> use has reached its peak and will decline.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究人员已经在调查机动车辆的使用是否已达到高峰，数量是否会下降。

examination_example.sentence: The founder of two tech companies, Tesla Motors and SpaceX, is bringing electric <highlight>vehicles</highlight> to mass market and enabling humans to live on other planets.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作为特斯拉汽车 (Tesla Motors) 和 SpaceX 两家科技公司的创始人，他正在将电动汽车推向大众市场，并使人类能够在其他星球上生活。

examination_example.sentence: There are currently around 155, 000 registered hybrid and electric <highlight>vehicles</highlight> on German roads, dwarfed by the 45 million gasoline and diesel cars.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 目前，德国道路上有大约15.5万辆登记的混合动力和电动汽车，与该国目前的4500万辆汽油和柴油汽车相比，简直是小巫见大巫。

examination_example.sentence: They will not reach their emissions goals by 2050 if they do not eliminate a large portion of <highlight>vehicle</highlight> emissions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果他们不消除大部分汽车排放问题，他们将无法在2050年达到排放目标。

examination_example.sentence: Many European countries have been making the shift to electric <highlight>vehicles</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 许多欧洲国家已经开始转向电动汽车。

examination_example.sentence: Other efforts to increase the use of electric <highlight>vehicles</highlight> include plans to build over 1 million hybrid.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 其他努力增加电动汽车使用的措施包括: 计划在全国建立超过100万个混合动力。

examination_example.sentence: They will not allow any gasoline-powered <highlight>vehicle</highlight> to be registered after 2030.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 2030年后，他们将不允许任何汽油驱动的车辆注册。

examination_example.sentence: As a result, books are often a better <highlight>vehicle</highlight> for transforming beliefs than conversations or debates.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 因此，书籍往往是一种比对话或辩论更好的转变观念的工具。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

examination_example.sentence: He says he built South Korea a luxury <highlight>vehicle</highlight>, like Mercedes or BMW.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他说，他为韩国打造了一辆豪华车，就像奔驰或宝马一样。

examination_example.sentence: If all four bills pass as written, they would represent a substantial update of Michigan's 2013 law that allowed the testing of self-driving <highlight>vehicles</highlight> in limited conditions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果这四项法案都能以书面形式通过，这就表示密西根在2013年制定的无人驾驶测试制度会发生实质性更新。

examination_example.sentence: It has migrated from Detroit to Silicon Valley, where self-driving <highlight>vehicles</highlight> are coming into life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它已经从底特律转移到了硅谷，在那里，自动驾驶汽车正在成为现实。

examination_example.sentence: In many European countries, where diesel (柴油) <highlight>vehicles</highlight> have become more common in recent years, that number reaches tens of thousands.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 近年来，在许多欧洲国家，柴油汽车变得更加普遍，达到数万辆。

examination_example.sentence: The companies developing self-driving <highlight>vehicles</highlight> should be partnering with state and federal authorities to offer retraining for this massive workforce, many of whom will be displaced by the new technology.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 开发自动驾驶车辆的公司应该与州和联邦当局合作，为这一庞大的劳动力提供再培训，其中，许多人将被新技术取代。

examination_example.sentence: There's no question that self-driving <highlight>vehicles</highlight> could be an enormous benefit.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 毫无疑问，自动驾驶汽车可以带来巨大的好处。

examination_example.sentence: Electric and gasoline <highlight>vehicles</highlight> look similar on the outside.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 电动和汽油车的外观看起来很相似。

examination_example.sentence: Electric <highlight>vehicles</highlight> are energy efficient, also making them cheaper to operate.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 电动汽车是节能的，也使其运行成本更低。

examination_example.sentence: If the tiniest piece of junk crashed into a spaceship, it could damage the <highlight>vehicle</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果最小的一块垃圾撞上宇宙飞船，可能会损坏飞船。
